    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I wrote a test to create the scenario described in this bug without success. Looking further, I noticed that the completion queue in ObjectiveC is constantly polled in a while loop. This makes C core notice the goaway and connection issues without needing to spin another completion queue or starting a watcher. See here https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/master/src/objective-c/GRPCClient/private/GRPCCompletionQueue.m#L69\nThis bug is actually not a valid bug. I propose closing. @jcanizales , @ctiller - any objections?\n"
  },
